<!-- VASA -->
<article class="event" id="event-vasa">
  <header>
    <h3><time datetime="1628">1628</time> — The Vasa</h3>
  </header>
  <p>
    The Swedish warship <cite>Vasa</cite> sank twenty minutes into its maiden voyage
    in Stockholm harbor. A stability test conducted before launch — men running side
    to side across the deck — was making the ship visibly rock so badly the test was
    stopped. King Gustav II Adolf had ordered the ship built with an extra gun deck
    against the advice of the original designer. Nobody with authority wanted to be
    the one to say it was not seaworthy. The hood was there. Opening it fully was
    the problem.
  </p>
